article.linkText: Adebayo's 16 lead Mount St. Mary's over Siena 68-61
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. -- — Dola Adebayo scored 16 points as Mount St. Mary's beat Siena 68-61 on Sunday. Adebayo added seven rebounds for the Mountaineers (9-13, 5-6 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Dakota Leffew scored 13 points while going 4 of 14 and 4 of 6 from the free-throw line, and added nine rebounds and four blocks. Dallas Hobbs shot 3 for 4, including 2 for 3 from beyond the arc to finish with eight points. Michael Eley led the way for the Saints (3-19, 2-9) with 24 points and two steals. Siena also got 14 points, six rebounds and three blocks from Michael Ojo. In addition, Giovanni Emejuru had 11 points and two steals. The loss is the sixth in a row for the Saints. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
